<section class="page-header">
<div class="container">
<p style="margin-bottom:8px;"><a href="/blog/" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.7);font-size:0.9rem;text-decoration:none;">&larr; Back to Blog</a></p>
<h1>July 4th Group Travel: Why You Should Book Your Van Early</h1>
<p>The single busiest van-rental weekend of the year. If you want to keep your group together for the holiday, the time to reserve is now.</p>
</div>
</section>
<section class="section">
<div class="container">
<div style="max-width:800px;margin:0 auto;">
<p>Every year it's the same story. Someone in the family volunteers to organize the July 4th get-together — the lake house, the cookout, the fireworks — and then realizes a week before the holiday that getting everyone there in one piece means either a four-car caravan or finding a vehicle big enough to hold the whole crew. By then, the vans are gone.</p>
<p>At <strong>Riverside Auto Rental</strong>, the <a href="/rent-local" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:600;">independent, family-owned car rental</a> in Black River Falls since 1983, the week of July 4th is our highest-demand stretch of the entire year. The 15-passenger vans book out first, usually by mid-June. This post is the friendly nudge: if a group trip is anywhere in your July 4th plans, reserve the vehicle now.</p>
<h2>Why July 4th is different from a normal weekend</h2>
<p>Three things collide on Independence Day weekend that make it the toughest rental weekend to plan for:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:24px;padding-left:20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><strong>It's a fixed date, not a flexible one.</strong> Everyone wants the vehicle for the same three or four days. There's no spreading demand across the month.</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><strong>Groups are bigger.</strong> Holiday gatherings pull in extended family, out-of-town guests, and friends-of-friends. A vehicle that seats 5 doesn't cut it.</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:10px;"><strong>15-passenger vans are scarce.</strong> Most national chains stopped carrying them years ago. The few independents that still have them — us included — have a finite number, and they go fast.</li>
</ul>
<h2>What to book, by group size</h2>
<table class="rate-table" style="margin-bottom:32px;">
<thead>
<tr>
<th>Group Size</th>
<th>Best Pick</th>
<th>Book By</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr><td><strong>5&ndash;7 people</strong></td><td>7-Passenger Minivan</td><td>3&ndash;4 weeks ahead</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>8&ndash;15 people</strong></td><td>15-Passenger Van</td><td>4&ndash;6 weeks ahead</td></tr>
<tr><td><strong>2&ndash;4 people, long drive</strong></td><td>Full-Size Car, Unlimited</td><td>2&ndash;3 weeks ahead</td></tr>
</tbody>
</table>
<p>For the July 4th holiday specifically, today (early June) is the right time to lock in a 15-passenger van. Minivans have a little more breathing room, but not much.</p>
<h2>The holiday-weekend logistics that actually matter</h2>
<p><strong>One vehicle beats a caravan.</strong> Fireworks traffic, packed lake-town parking, and "wait, which car has the cooler?" all disappear when the group rides together. You park once and everyone walks in together.</p>
<p><strong>Designated driver, simplified.</strong> July 4th cookouts tend to involve a few cold ones. With one van and one driver, the rest of the group relaxes and nobody's doing math about who's okay to drive home.</p>
<p><strong>Cargo for the whole spread.</strong> Coolers, lawn chairs, the grill, the fireworks, the kids' floaties — a 15-passenger van with the back rows configured for cargo swallows all of it.</p>
<h2>Our holiday hours and pickup timing</h2>
<p>Plan around our hours:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:24px;padding-left:20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">Monday&ndash;Friday: <strong>8:00 AM &ndash; 5:00 PM</strong></li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">Saturday: <strong>8:00 AM &ndash; 12:00 PM (noon)</strong></li>
<li style="margin-bottom:8px;">Sunday &amp; July 4th holiday: <strong>Closed / by appointment</strong></li>
</ul>
<p>The standard July 4th rental is a <strong>Friday pickup, Monday or Tuesday return</strong>. If you need a Sunday or holiday-day pickup, arrange it during the week beforehand and we'll set up an appointment.</p>
<h2>A typical July 4th van rental</h2>
<div style="background:var(--off-white);border:1px solid var(--light-gray);border-radius:var(--radius-lg);padding:28px;margin-bottom:32px;">
<h3 style="margin-bottom:16px;">4-Day Rental &mdash; 15-Passenger Van</h3>
<p style="margin:0 0 12px 0;">Friday pickup &rarr; Tuesday return. Extended family of 12 for a lake-house weekend.</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 4px 0;"><strong>Weekly rate:</strong> $750 (unlimited mileage, covers the full 4-day window)</p>
<p style="margin:0 0 4px 0;"><strong>vs. Daily:</strong> ($135 &times; 4) + mileage = $540 + ~$40 for 400 mi = ~$580</p>
<p style="margin:0;"><strong>The call:</strong> Daily wins for a short, low-mileage weekend; weekly wins once you cross ~5 days or pile on the miles. We'll do the math with you.</p>
</div>
<p>For the full daily-vs-weekly breakdown, see our <a href="/blog/weekly-car-rental-rates-when-7-days-beats-daily.html" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:600;">weekly rate guide</a>.</p>
<h2>What you'll need to reserve</h2>
<p>To hold a van on the calendar, all we need is a name, a contact number, and your approximate dates. No deposit required to reserve. At pickup, bring:</p>
<ul style="margin-bottom:24px;padding-left:20px;">
<li style="margin-bottom:10px;">Valid U.S. driver's license</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:10px;">Major credit card or bank-issued debit card linked to a checking account</li>
<li style="margin-bottom:10px;">Proof of auto insurance (policy number and expiration date)</li>
</ul>
<h2>What our renters say</h2>
<div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;margin-bottom:16px;">
<span style="color:#f59e0b;font-size:1.1rem;letter-spacing:1px;" aria-label="5 out of 5 stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</span>
<span style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:600;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">5.0 on Google</span>
</div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-left:4px solid var(--navy);border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
<p style="font-style:italic;color:var(--text);line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px;">"I rented a 15-passenger van for a family trip taking my daughters to a volleyball tournament in Kansas City. The entire rental process was completely seamless. Staff is super friendly, quick paperwork, and no hassle at all. The van was a perfect fit for our needs."</p>
<div style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Ben H. <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">&mdash; 15-Passenger Van for Group Travel</span></div>
</div>
<div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-left:4px solid var(--navy);border-radius:8px;padding:24px;margin-bottom:20px;">
