<div style="font-family:'Archivo',sans-serif;font-weight:700;color:var(--navy);">Sal H. <span style="font-weight:400;color:var(--text-light);font-size:0.9rem;">&mdash; 7-Passenger Minivan Rental</span></div>
</div>
<p style="margin-bottom:32px;"><a href="https://search.google.com/local/reviews?placeid=ChIJe_gqTAjn_ocRVVpllXYH-zQ" target="_blank" rel="noopener" style="color:var(--navy);font-weight:600;">Read all reviews on Google &rarr;</a></p>
<h2>Don't wait on this one</h2>
<p>July 4th is the one weekend where "I'll call next week" turns into "they're all booked." If a group trip is in your plans, reserve the van today. Call <a href="tel:+17153961466"><strong>715-396-1466</strong></a> with your dates and we'll hold it — no deposit required.</p>
<div style="margin-top:48px;">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
<div class="faq-list">
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">How early should I book a van for July 4th weekend?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>4 to 6 weeks ahead for a 15-passenger van, 3 to 4 weeks for a minivan. By mid-June, holiday-weekend vans are usually fully booked.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">What does a 15-passenger van cost for the holiday weekend?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>$135/day plus $0.10/mile, or $750/week with unlimited mileage. The weekly rate is usually the better value for a 5+ day or high-mileage holiday trip.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">Are you open over the July 4th holiday?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>Open Friday and Saturday morning; closed Sunday and the holiday itself. Holiday pickups/returns can be arranged by appointment in advance. Friday pickup, Monday/Tuesday return is the standard.</p></div>
</div>
<div class="faq-item">
<button class="faq-question" aria-expanded="false">Do you still carry 15-passenger vans?
<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><line x1="12" y1="5" x2="12" y2="19"/><line x1="5" y1="12" x2="19" y2="12"/></svg>
</button>
<div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes &mdash; we're one of the few providers in western Wisconsin still carrying them for consumer rental. That scarcity is exactly why holiday weekends book up so fast.</p></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
